channel.title: Java question about starting your program faster
channel.description:
Well I'm still completely new to java, learning the basics, and I was wondering this:
If I create a custom method & have the main call that method, will the program run faster?
I'm not even sure if I should ask this question... but I'm completely new, so I'm asking it anyway :D

item.title: Java question about starting your program faster
item.dc:creator: @T41 t4
item.description:
@T41 wrote:

when calling a function, you’re going to a different part of the code (goto’s haha), so TECHNICALLY you suffer a slow down from doing this. i’m not suggesting not using functions at all, however… it’s EXTREMELY negligible.
